  "text": "The reduction of the first year mortality in the Brest Region NSCLC cohort may be explained by the increase of the number of patients who underwent the combination of platinum-based chemotherapy and radiotherapy from 7% in 2001 to 15% in 2011 as well as the increase of surgical treatment from 19% to 48% respectively. It is also supported by other authors that surgical treatment was associated with improved survival for both localized and regional advanced diseases [CITATION_1] .",
